

**Answer: 12168**

--------------------------------------------------------------------
### 1.  The spiral on a hexagonal grid  

The numbers are placed on a pointy‑top hex grid in the order  

```
East → North‑East → North‑West → West → South‑West → South‑East
```

 starting with 1 at the centre.  
For a given “layer’’ \(k\;(k=1,2,\dots )\) we walk \(k\) steps in each of the
six directions.  

The total number up to the end of layer \(k\) is  

\[
N_k = 1+6\bigl(1+2+\dots +k\bigr)=3k^2+3k+1 .
\]

The first number of layer \(k\) is \(N_{k-1}+1\) and layer \(k\) contains
\(6k\) cells.

--------------------------------------------------------------------
### 2.  Coordinates of a cell  

Use axial coordinates \((q,r)\) with the six neighbour vectors  

\[
\begin{aligned}
E      &= ( +1,0), & NE =( 0,-1),\\
NW    &= (-1,-1), & W  = (-1,0),\\
SW    &= ( 0, +1),& SE = (+1,+1) .
\end{aligned}
\]

For a point that lies on the **North‑West** side of its layer we have

\[
r\le -2,\qquad q\ge0,\qquad 
k = q-r-1 .
\]

The offset (position inside its layer) of such a point is  

\[
\text{offset}=2k-r-1=3k-q .
\]

The number written there is  

\[
n = N_{k-1} + \text{offset}.
\]

--------------------------------------------------------------------
### 3.  Locate 2026  

Since  

\[
3k^2+3k+1\ge 2026\quad\Longrightarrow\quad k=26,
\]

2026 belongs to layer \(k=26\).  
Its offset in that layer is  

\[
2026- N_{25}=2026-1951=75 ,
\]

which indeed lies on the North‑West side (\(53\le\!75\le78\)).  
Solving the equations of the North‑West side gives the coordinates

\[
(q,r)=(3,-24).
\]

--------------------------------------------------------------------
### 4.  The six neighbours  

The neighbours are obtained by adding the six direction vectors:

\[
\begin{array}{c|c}
\text{direction} & (q,r)\\ \hline
E   & (4,-24)\\
NE  & (3,-25)\\
NW  & (2,-25)\\
W   & (2,-24)\\
SW  & (3,-23)\\
SE  & (4,-23)
\end{array}
\]

Each of them lies on a North‑West side as well; we determine its layer
\(k\) and offset with the formulas above.

| neighbour | \(k\) | offset | number |
|-----------|------|--------|--------|
| (4,-24)   | 27   | 77     | \(N_{26}+77 = 2107+77 = 2184\) |
| (3,-25)   | 27   | 78     | \(2107+78 = 2185\) |
| (2,-25)   | 26   | 76     | \(N_{25}+76 = 1951+76 = 2027\) |
| (2,-24)   | 25   | 73     | \(N_{24}+73 = 1801+73 = 1874\) |
| (3,-23)   | 25   | 72     | \(1801+72 = 1873\) |
| (4,-23)   | 26   | 74     | \(1951+74 = 2025\) |

--------------------------------------------------------------------
### 5.  Sum of the neighbours  

\[
\begin{aligned}
\text{Sum}&=2184+2185+2027+1874+1873+2025\\
          &=12168 .
\end{aligned}
\]

--------------------------------------------------------------------
\[
\boxed{12168}
\]
